# Gate
  `ruins_visits++`
  > The watchtower gate leans open between two stones carved like sleeping dogs.
  > `lantern_lit` Your lantern paints warm teeth along the archway stones.
  *-> `!lantern_lit && !heard_bell_rumor` [.LoseNerve]
  -> [.Approach]

## LoseNerve
  > The darkness beneath the arch presses against your face until you step back gasping.
  + Return to the village -> [Village]("/main.saga")

## Approach
  > Your lantern throws gold over a stair spiraling down under the tower.
  + Descend into the courtyard -> [Courtyard]
  + Search the gatehouse -> [.Gatehouse]
  + Return to Brindlewick -> [Village]("/main.saga")

### Gatehouse
  `found_chalk ?= false`
  > The gatehouse roof has collapsed, but a dry shelf remains beneath a slab of slate.
  + Take the white chalk *-> [.TakeChalk]
  + Return to the gate -> [Gate.Approach]

#### TakeChalk
  `found_chalk := true`
  > You pocket a stick of white chalk. It leaves a moon-pale smear on your thumb.
  -> [Gate.Approach]

# Courtyard
  > The sunken courtyard lies open to the rain. Four doors wait under four broken arches.
  > `found_chalk` The chalk in your pocket leaves a pale crescent on your fingertips.
  + Inspect the well -> [.Well]
  + Enter the archive -> [.Archive]
  + Try the lower door -> `old_key` [.LowerDoor]
  + `!old_key` Examine the sealed lower door -> [.SealedDoor]
  + Retreat to the gate -> [Gate]

## Well
  `well_echo = rand(100)`
  > You lean over the well. Far below, water repeats your breathing.
  *-> `well_echo > 70` [.CoinGlimmer]
  -> [.QuietWater]

### CoinGlimmer
  `coin := coin + 1`
  > Something bright spins up from the dark, lands at your feet, and becomes a coin.
  -> [..QuietWater]

### QuietWater
  > The well gives nothing back but the small sound of rain.
  -> [Courtyard]

## Archive
  > Shelves of stone tablets lean against the walls. Most are blank with age.
  > `knows_mark` You keep searching for a bell inside a closed eye.
  + Look for the archivist's mark -> `knows_mark` [.MarkedTablet]
  + Search randomly -> [.RandomTablet]
  + Return to the courtyard -> [Courtyard]

### MarkedTablet
  `archive_mark := true`
  > You find the bell-in-eye mark. When you knock twice, a hidden drawer opens.
  + Take the bronze tongue *-> [.BronzeTongue]
  + Leave the drawer alone -> [Courtyard.Archive]

#### BronzeTongue
  `bronze_tongue := true`
  > The bronze tongue is cold and heavy, made for a bell that should not still exist.
  -> [Courtyard.Archive]

### RandomTablet
  `dust_count++`
  > Dust coats your hands. The tablets say nothing you understand.
  + Keep searching -> `dust_count < 3` [.RandomTablet]
  + Give up -> [Courtyard.Archive]

## SealedDoor
  > The lower door has no handle, only a keyhole shaped like a crooked tooth.
  + Return to the courtyard -> [Courtyard]

## LowerDoor
  > The blackened key turns with a sound like a cough.
  > `lower_door_hint` You remember the locksmith's warning and work slowly.
  *-> `lower_door_hint && lantern_lit` [.OiledLock]
  -> [.StubbornLock]

### StubbornLock
  > The lock resists you. Rust flakes fall like old scabs.
  + Return to the courtyard -> [Courtyard]

### OiledLock
  > The lock remembers the key. The lower door opens inward.
  + Enter the bell chamber -> [Chamber]("/bell.saga")
